channel.title: Helps =P
channel.description: ok i just re installed windows yesterday i set up all my ips again (defualt, gateway ect...) anyways everything should be perfect but no one and not even me can sign onto my server yes it is on. my fire wall is off also and i dont know what the problem is? anyone know?

item.title: Helps =P
item.dc:creator: @openice123 openice123
item.description:
@openice123 wrote:

[quote=“n0va k0, post:2, topic:184077”][quote author=openice123 link=topic=245755.msg2072639#msg2072639 date=1203808728]
ok i just re installed windows yesterday i set up all my ips again (defualt, gateway ect…)
anyways everything should be perfect but no one and not even me can sign onto my server
yes it is on.
my fire wall is off also and i dont know what the problem is?
anyone know?
[/quote]
Well >.> We’ll have to start from the small stuff to the bigger stuff.

1.When you said you couldn’t log onto your own server, what did you put for server ip?
2. Sure that your ip never changed overtime when you didn’t have windows?
3. What kind of router do you have if you have one anyways. If it is wireless, a few things you can do. Find that blue cord in the back and (your on your own >.> I was going to do this but didn’t want to risk) You can’t portforward on a wireless router on a computer unless it is a laptop.

I can’t help you much unless it is linksys[/quote]

-.- dont need to type in your ip for your own server
it took 4 hours to re-install it highly doubt it changed
dont think its my router cus ive had my server for over 7 months
